    "body": "Well, I wouldn't suggest going with an actual BUILD file to build OpenSSL from the source, that'd be a bit... overwhelming. What I'd suggest however is to use the trick that you can specify a .a library as a source file.\n\nSo what you can do is the following: build OpenSSL from sources using its ./Configure script, with the appropriate install prefix so that it installs somewhere into your project's workspace. From here, your BUILD file is simply something along these lines:\n\n```\ncc_library(\n    name = \"openssl\",\n    srcs = glob([\"lib/*.a\"]),\n    hdrs = glob([\"include/*.h\"]),\n)\n```\n"
  },
