    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I don't think grpc should rely on external dependencies unless it explicitly specifies in the documentation what those external dependencies are and how they can be added. For example, I was only able to find information on them within [Tensorflow's workspace file](https://github.com/GPflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/workspace.bzl)\n\nEDIT: running in to this in multiple instances and it's making grpc pretty much unusable with bazel. Are there any currently open issues involving removing implicit external dependencies? This seems like a major bazel anti-pattern. Taking tensorflow's approach of a macro which generates appropriate workspace parameters seems like the way to go here.\n"
  },
